history.content:
The class has 1 open seat, according to http://classes.berkeley.edu/content/2017-fall-compsci-188-001-lec-001.

Presumably a glitch or from someone just dropping, since there's 67 students on the waitlist which would block you from directly enrolling anyway.

children.subject: No, being a CS or EECS major only gets you enrollment priority during phase 1 and phase 2. Check out the L&S FQA for a more detailed answer.
Even if this was Phase 1 or 2 and you had enrollment priority, the answer still would be no, since the class is full.
Thanks for the clarification, I was placed on waitlist #67. When my major is confirmed will I automatically get into the class?
